  "body": "We currently try to sign all `validatorRegistration` concurrently, which is not a good strategy when remote signer is in use.\r\n\r\nWe have to consider the worse case in which we are already performing duties and we suddenly have to sign 1k `validatorRegistration` objects and we don't want to overload the signer (and outgoing tcp connections) with \"low priority\" signatures that are way less important than real duty signatures. This can cause delays or even timeouts that can lead to bad attestation performances.\r\n\r\n- Improvement 1: limit the signing concurrency.\r\nSo an improvement could be to split the validators stream in `ValidatorRegistrator#registerValidators` batches and `collectAll` each batch before moving to the next batch, so we well have a cap on the number of concurrent sign requests.\r\n\r\nAnother, more structural, approach could be to implement a throttling on the outgoing external signer requests (which will apply on all requests). But it would be difficult to decide the actual limit and will require to implement a priority scheme which should give precedence to signature on duties over the validator signatures.\r\n\r\n- Improvement 2: better handling of signing errors (ie timeouts)\r\nWe currently fail the entire flow if we have just one failing signing future. We should let the registration process continue excluding the failed ones (will be retried automatically the next round)",
